16 people were injured after a collision between a minibus taxi and a light motor vehicle on Saturday morning. 
The crash took place in Amanzimtoti, south of Durban. 
Paramedics at the scene of the crash. Image: Twitter/@_ArriveAlive
Image: Twitter/@_ArriveAlive
Netcare911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said the injuries ranged from minor to moderate, and that once stabilised, patients were transported to nearby hospitals for further treatment. 
